<subSubSection pageId="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1757,2034]" pageId="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,445,1757,1782]" pageId="20">Taxonomic observations</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1912" box="[464,772,1757,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sedecimguttata">
<emphasis box="[464,772,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="20">Blepharida sedecimguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Weise, J." box="[999,1154,1757,1782]" pageId="20" pagination="76 - 98" refId="ref19046" refString="Weise, J. (1912) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Chrysomeliden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 78, 76 - 98." type="journal article" year="1912">Weise (1912)</bibRefCitation>
from Gawiro in Uhehe (
<collectingCountry box="[158,263,1793,1818]" name="Tanzania" pageId="20">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, Gairo 
<geoCoordinate box="[354,470,1793,1818]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="20" precision="15" value="-6.1349998">6°08′06''S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[485,618,1793,1818]" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="20" precision="15" value="36.86222">36°51′44''E</geoCoordinate>
). Neither the 
<typeStatus box="[781,829,1794,1818]" pageId="20">type</typeStatus>
nor other specimens attributed to this species were found in any examined collections. However, the description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Weise, J." box="[876,1026,1829,1854]" pageId="20" pagination="76 - 98" refId="ref19046" refString="Weise, J. (1912) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Chrysomeliden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 78, 76 - 98." type="journal article" year="1912">Weise (1912)</bibRefCitation>
leaves no doubt about its attribution to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Iannella &amp; Biondi" authorityYear="2019" box="[296,444,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[296,444,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="20">Blepharidina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as its similarity with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[786,886,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rudeli">
<emphasis box="[786,886,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="20">B. rudeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1912" box="[900,1103,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sedecimguttata">
<emphasis box="[900,1103,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="20">B. sedecimguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rudeli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20">B. rudeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the: eight large yellow patches on each elytron, as well as a small yellow patch in the shoulder angle before the humeral callus, with only one patch in front of the apex (nine large yellow patches, with two patches in front of the apex in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[388,489,1973,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Blepharidina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rudeli">
<emphasis box="[388,489,1973,1997]" italics="true" pageId="20">B. rudeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); more finely impressed elytral punctation; more sparsely stained pronotum, with shorter longitudinal furrows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,151,176]" pageId="21">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[359,460,151,176]" name="Tanzania" pageId="21">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[475,559,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–69" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1661,1684]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,374,1634]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,374,1640]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 68–69. Blepharidina s. str. species distribution. Vegetation types are from Sayre et al. (2013)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618655/files/figure.png" pageId="21">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Possibly Northern-Eastern Afrotropical (NEA) chorotype. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,396,188,213]" pageId="21">Ecological notes</emphasis>
. Not available. The collection site falls within the area of Eastern African Xeric Scrub (belonging to the Warm Desert &amp; Semi-Desert Scrub &amp; Grassland formation).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
